  "result": "Here's a summary of the changes made to fix the SVG CSS update via JavaScript incorrect rendering issue:\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe issue is a **same-origin policy violation**. The card viewer page is served from `http://127.0.0.1:PORT/`, but the `parseSourcesToFileScheme()` function converts `<object data=\"_keyboard.svg\">` to `<object data=\"file:///path/to/media/_keyboard.svg\">`. When JavaScript tries to access `obj.contentDocument`, the browser blocks it because `http://127.0.0.1` and `file:///` are different origins.\n\nThis is why the error `\"Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'querySelectorAll')\"` occurs \u2014 `contentDocument` returns `null` due to the cross-origin restriction.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/libanki/TemplateManager.kt` (line 371)\n\nRemoved `<object>` tags from the file scheme conversion. The `<object>` tag was being treated like `<img>`, `<audio>`, and `<video>`, but unlike those tags (which benefit from `file:///` for media seeking), `<object>` tags create a nested browsing context that JavaScript needs to access via `contentDocument`. By keeping the relative URL, the `<object>` content is served from the same `http://127.0.0.1:PORT/` origin as the main page.\n\n### 2. `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/ViewerAssetLoader.kt` (line 39-40)\n\nAdded `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` CORS header to the `WebResourceResponse` returned for media files. This ensures that cross-origin requests from within `<object>` elements (e.g., the SVG fetching resources, or JavaScript making requests) succeed. This is safe because the asset loader only serves local media files on localhost.",
